jobPostings.title: Junior Configuration Analyst
jobPostings.description:
About BQI Tech

We are software development and technology professional service company that specializes in delivering modern solutions and services to the State and Local Government in the Land Management, Business Licensing, Professional Licensing, and Asset Management spaces.


We’re seeking talented and self-motivated individuals who are passionate about customer satisfaction and have a keen eye for detail. Join us in delivering successful solutions in the e-governments space.


About the role

  • Review captured business requirements
  • Configure solutions that meet customer needs based on stories entered in JIRA or developed in Microsoft Word
  • Develop, test, and document completed solutions
  • Provide end user and technical documents on completed solutions
  • Participate in other technical components (Scripting, Data Conversion/Migration, Report Development)

About You

  • 2+ years of configuration consulting experience with Commercial off the Shelf (COTS) software
  • 2+ years Report Development using SSRS or Crystal Reports
  • 1+ years' experience converting or migrating data between COTS systems using ETL tools
  • Land Management, Business Licensing, Professional Licensing, Code Enforcement experience
  • Bachelor's degree in information technology or related field
  • Strong written and verbal communication
  • Strong presentation experience
  • Experience with both Agile and Waterfall methodologies
  • JavaScript experience
  • SQL Script experience (Oracle or SQL Server)
  • Javascript knowledge

Benefits

  • Comprehensive private medical insurance
  • Pension
  • Annual bonus
  • Competitive holiday + Birtholiday


Female candidates are strongly encouraged to apply
